                            "<li><strong>Diverting Resources:</strong> Forward's CEO Alex deliberately diverts resources away from the primary \"meals served\" metric to partner with a local legal clinic.</li>" +
                            "<li><strong>The Invisibility of Care:</strong> In a managerialist system, this appears highly inefficient. As David Beer notes, <em>\"measurement draws attention to certain things... whilst pulling our gaze away from other aspects of the social and the personal.\"</em><sup>1</sup></li>" +
                            "<li><strong>Community Reciprocity:</strong> By focusing on unquantifiable legal wellbeing rather than raw volume, Forward engages in <em>\"community reciprocity.\"</em><sup>2</sup></li>" +
                            "<li><strong>Asset Diversification:</strong> Forward builds a multidimensional safety net, diversifying its assets, while Apex over-leverages a single, fragile metric.</li>" +
                          "</ul>",
                    citation: "<div style='margin-bottom: 8px;'>[1] Beer, David. 2016. <em>Metric Power</em>. London: Palgrave Macmillan, 60.</div><div>[2] Witmer, Hope, and Marcela Sarmiento Mellinger. 2016. \"Organizational Resilience: Nonprofit Organizations' Response to Change.\" <em>Work</em> 54: 255-265.</div>"
                }
            },
            5: {
                0: {
                    theme: 'theme-red',
                    title: "The Cat-and-Mouse Game",
                    text: "<ul class='concept-text-list'>" +
                            "<li><strong>The Illusion of Success:</strong> While the city views Apex as a triumph, internal leadership and staff are locked in a dangerous game for <em>\"control over meaning.\"</em><sup>1</sup></li>" +
                            "<li><strong>Competing Motives:</strong> The organization desperately seeks <em>\"an accurate and meaningful reflection of activity.\"</em><sup>1</sup></li>" +
                            "<li><strong>Worker Adaptation:</strong> Conversely, workers under intense pressure adapt by <em>\"shaping the communication of activity in ways that meets situated goals\"</em><sup>1</sup> (e.g., survival and avoiding termination).</li>" +
                          "</ul>",
                    citation: "[1] Treem, Jeffrey W., William C. Barley, Matthew S. Weber, and Joshua B. Barbour. 2023. \"Signaling and Meaning in Organizational Analytics: Coping with Goodhart's Law in an Era of Digitization and Datafication.\" <em>Journal of Computer-Mediated Communication</em> 28 (4): 9."
                }
            },
            6: {
                0: {
                    theme: 'theme-red',
                    title: "Dubious Signaling",
                    text: "<ul class='concept-text-list'>" +
                            "<li><strong>Dishonest Metrics:</strong> Apex's massive growth is a dubious signal. Under extreme pressure, workers gamed the system to achieve genuine but profoundly dishonest numbers.</li>" +
                            "<li><strong>Mission Decoupling:</strong> Robbie's technology hack completely <em>\"decoupled\"</em><sup>1</sup> the data tracking from the broad mission of protecting the vulnerable.</li>" +
                            "<li><strong>A Breach of Public Trust:</strong> Honesty only at the point of service delivery following a dishonest process is dubious signaling.</li>" +
                            "<li><strong>Questionable Data:</strong> The metric is fundamentally compromised because Robbie <em>\"engage[d] in behaviors with the goal of producing... questionable data.\"</em><sup>1</sup></li>" +
                          "</ul>",
                    citation: "[1] Treem, Jeffrey W., William C. Barley, Matthew S. Weber, and Joshua B. Barbour. 2023. \"Signaling and Meaning in Organizational Analytics: Coping with Goodhart's Law in an Era of Digitization and Datafication.\" <em>Journal of Computer-Mediated Communication</em> 28 (4): 3."
                }
            },
            8: {
                1: {
                    theme: 'theme-blue',
                    title: "Organizational Resilience",
                    text: "<ul class='concept-text-list'>" +
                            "<li><strong>Absorbing the Shockwave:</strong> While Apex's fragile, metric-gamed foundation paralyzes its operations, Forward's diversified community assets absorb the sector-wide freeze.</li>" +
                            "<li><strong>Continuity of Service:</strong> The legal clinic partnership maintains communication with beneficiaries, ensuring continuity of service and providing an impervious safety net.</li>" +
                            "<li><strong>Defining Resilience:</strong> Organizational resilience is <em>\"the ability of an organization to respond and adapt to incremental changes and sudden disruptions while also constantly anticipating and preparing for future challenges in order to sustainably meet [the organization's] mission.\"</em><sup>1</sup></li>" +
                          "</ul>",
                    citation: "[1] Miller-Stevens, Katrina, Zachariah Benevento-Zahner, Gabrielle L'Esperance, and Jennifer A. Taylor. 2022. \"Assessing Multidimensional Approaches to Measure Program Outcomes in Human Service Organizations.\" <em>Voluntas: International Journal of Voluntary and Nonprofit Organizations</em> 33: 1214."
                }
            },
            9: {
                1: {
                    theme: 'theme-blue',
                    title: "Relational Slack Resources",
                    text: "<ul class='concept-text-list'>" +
                            "<li><strong>The Cost of Perfect Efficiency:</strong> Apex's fatal flaw was optimizing for perfect business efficiency without investing in long-term, interorganizational connections.</li>" +
                            "<li><strong>Vulnerability Without Slack:</strong> Eliminating relational slack to hit a quota left Apex completely vulnerable to scandal, with no outside social capital to survive.</li>" +
                            "<li><strong>Inefficiency as a Buffer:</strong> Forward's slower, relationship-based approach appeared inefficient, but it successfully generated vital <em>\"organizational slack.\"</em><sup>1</sup></li>" +
                            "<li><strong>Adaptation and Survival:</strong> This relational slack acts as a crucial buffer, providing the resources and flexibility required to adapt when externally-controlled systems collapse.</li>" +
                          "</ul>",
                    citation: "[1] Witmer, Hope, and Marcela Sarmiento Mellinger. 2016. \"Organizational Resilience: Nonprofit Organizations' Response to Change.\" <em>Work</em> 54: 255-265. https://doi.org/10.3233/WOR-162303."
                }
            }
        };

        // --- Custom Plugin for Warning & Coffin Icons ---
        const annotationsPlugin = {
            id: 'annotations',
            afterDatasetsDraw(chart) {
                const ctx = chart.ctx;
                const datasetIndex = 0; 
                const meta = chart.getDatasetMeta(datasetIndex);

                ctx.save();
                ctx.font = '24px Arial';
                ctx.textAlign = 'center';
                ctx.textBaseline = 'bottom';

                if (chart.data.labels.length - 1 >= 7) {
                    const point7 = meta.data[7];
                    if (point7) ctx.fillText('⚠️', point7.x, point7.y - 12);
                }
                if (chart.data.labels.length - 1 >= 12) {
                    const point12 = meta.data[12];
                    if (point12) ctx.fillText('⚰️', point12.x, point12.y - 12);
                }
                ctx.restore();
            }
        };

        // --- Chart Setup ---
        const ctx = document.getElementById('impactChart').getContext('2d');
        const impactChart = new Chart(ctx, {
            type: 'line',
            data: {
                labels: labels.slice(0, 1),
                datasets: [
                    {
                        label: 'Apex Metro Relief',
                        data: unethicalData.slice(0, 1),
                        borderColor: '#ef4444', 
                        backgroundColor: 'rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.1)',
                        borderWidth: 3,
                        tension: 0.3,
                        fill: true,
                        segment: {
                            borderDash: ctx => ctx.p0DataIndex >= 11 ? [5, 5] : undefined,
                            borderColor: ctx => ctx.p0DataIndex >= 11 ? 'rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.3)' : '#ef4444',
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        label: 'Forward Community Pantry',
                        data: ethicalData.slice(0, 1),
                        borderColor: '#3b82f6', 
                        backgroundColor: 'rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.1)',
                        borderWidth: 3,
                        tension: 0.3,
                        fill: true
                    }
                ]
            },
            options: {
                responsive: true,
                animation: { duration: 400 },
                scales: {
                    y: {
                        min: 0,
                        max: 1200000, 
                        title: { display: true, text: 'Cumulative Meals Served' }
                    }
                },
                // Interactivity: Click Specific Dots to Review Concepts
                onClick: (event, activeElements) => {
                    if (activeElements.length > 0) {
                        const el = activeElements[0];
                        const yearConcepts = academicConcepts[el.index];
                        // Ensure they clicked the correct dataset point for that year
                        if (yearConcepts && yearConcepts[el.datasetIndex]) {
                            if (!isPaused) {
                                isPaused = true;
                                updateButtons();
                                showAcademicConcept(el.index, el.datasetIndex, true); 
                            }
                        }
                    }
                }
            },
            plugins: [annotationsPlugin]
        });

        // --- Control State & UI Variables ---
        const slider = document.getElementById('yearSlider');
        const prevBtn = document.getElementById('prevBtn');
        const nextBtn = document.getElementById('nextBtn');
        const yearLabel = document.getElementById('yearLabel');
        const eventCards = {
            2: document.getElementById('event-2'),
            4: document.getElementById('event-4'),
            7: document.getElementById('event-7'),
            10: document.getElementById('event-10'),
            12: document.getElementById('event-12'),
            13: document.getElementById('event-13')
        };

        let isPaused = true; 
        let hasSeenBreach = false;
        let hasSeenCrash = false;
        let hasSeenDeath = false;
        
        // Track academic popups
        let seenConcepts = { 2: false, 3: false, 4: false, 5: false, 6: false, 8: false, 9: false };

        document.getElementById('narrative').innerText = narratives[0];
        updateButtons();

        function updateButtons() {
            const val = parseInt(slider.value);
            prevBtn.disabled = val === 0 || isPaused;
            nextBtn.disabled = val === 13 || isPaused;
            slider.disabled = isPaused;
        }

        function updateHistory(index) {
            const list = document.getElementById('history-list');
            list.innerHTML = '';
            for(let i=0; i<=index; i++) {
                const li = document.createElement('li');
                li.innerHTML = `<strong>Year ${i}:</strong> ${narratives[i].substring(narratives[i].indexOf(':') + 2)}`;
                list.appendChild(li);
            }
        }

        // --- Swooping Modal Logic ---
        function triggerSwoop(text, yearIndex) {
            const floater = document.getElementById('floating-narrative');
            const target = document.getElementById('narrative');
            const btn = document.getElementById('fn-btn');
            
            floater.style.transition = 'none';
            floater.style.top = '40%';
            floater.style.left = '50%';
            floater.style.transform = 'translate(-50%, -50%) scale(1)';
            floater.style.display = 'block';
            void floater.offsetWidth; 
            floater.style.opacity = '1';
            
            document.getElementById('fn-text').innerText = text;
            target.style.opacity = '0.3';
            target.innerText = text; 

            isPaused = true;
            updateButtons();

            btn.onclick = () => {
                const targetRect = target.getBoundingClientRect();
                const floaterRect = floater.getBoundingClientRect();
                const deltaY = targetRect.top - floaterRect.top;
                
                floater.style.transition = 'all 0.6s cubic-bezier(0.25, 1, 0.5, 1)';
                floater.style.transform = `translate(-50%, calc(-50% + ${deltaY + 20}px)) scale(0.8)`;
                floater.style.opacity = '0';
                
                setTimeout(() => {
                    floater.style.display = 'none';
                    target.style.opacity = '1';
                    
                    updateHistory(yearIndex);
                    isPaused = false;
                    updateButtons();
                }, 600); 
            };
        }

        // --- Core Update Function ---
        function updateChartAndUI(index) {
            yearLabel.innerText = index;

            for (let year in eventCards) {
                eventCards[year].style.display = index >= parseInt(year) ? 'block' : 'none';
            }

            const targetMax = index === 13 ? 3000000 : 1200000;
            if (impactChart.options.scales.y.max !== targetMax) {
                impactChart.options.scales.y.max = targetMax;
            }

            impactChart.data.labels = labels.slice(0, index + 1);
            impactChart.data.datasets[0].data = unethicalData.slice(0, index + 1);
            impactChart.data.datasets[1].data = ethicalData.slice(0, index + 1);
            impactChart.update();
        }

        // --- Cinematic Controllers ---
        function dismissIntro() {
            document.getElementById('intro-overlay').style.opacity = '0';
            setTimeout(() => { 
                document.getElementById('intro-overlay').style.display = 'none'; 
                triggerSwoop(narratives[0], 0);
            }, 500);
        }

        function nextBreachOverlay(currentStep) {
            document.getElementById(`breach-overlay-${currentStep}`).style.display = 'none';
            document.getElementById(`breach-overlay-${currentStep + 1}`).style.display = 'flex';
            if (currentStep === 1) {
                document.getElementById('breach-overlay-2').style.opacity = '1';
            }
        }

        function finishBreachOverlay() {
            const overlay = document.getElementById('breach-overlay-3');
            overlay.style.opacity = '0';
            setTimeout(() => { 
                overlay.style.display = 'none'; 
                seenConcepts[2] = true;
                showAcademicConcept(2, 0, false); // Triggers Apex's concept
            }, 500);
        }

        function dismissCrash() {
            const overlay = document.getElementById('crash-overlay');
            overlay.style.opacity = '0';
            setTimeout(() => { 
                overlay.style.display = 'none'; 
                triggerSwoop(narratives[7], 7);
            }, 500);
        }

        function dismissDeath() {
            const overlay = document.getElementById('death-overlay');
            overlay.style.opacity = '0';
            window.speechSynthesis.cancel(); 
            setTimeout(() => { 
                overlay.style.display = 'none'; 
                triggerSwoop(narratives[12], 12);
            }, 500);
        }

        // --- Academic Concept Engine ---
        function showAcademicConcept(yearIndex, datasetIndex, isRetrigger = false) {
            const conceptInfo = academicConcepts[yearIndex][datasetIndex];
            const meta = impactChart.getDatasetMeta(datasetIndex);
            const point = meta.data[yearIndex];

            if (point) {
                const anchor = document.getElementById('concept-anchor');
                const box = document.getElementById('concept-box');
                const line = document.getElementById('concept-line');
                
                anchor.className = conceptInfo.theme;
                line.className = 'concept-line'; // Reset classes
                
                document.getElementById('concept-title').innerHTML = conceptInfo.title;
                document.getElementById('concept-text').innerHTML = conceptInfo.text;
                document.getElementById('concept-citation').innerHTML = conceptInfo.citation;

                // Smart Line Direction: If point is high (Years 5 and 6), shoot down to prevent cutoff
                if (yearIndex === 5 || yearIndex === 6) {
                    line.classList.add('shoot-down');
                    box.style.bottom = 'auto';
                    box.style.top = '40px';
                } else {
                    line.classList.add('shoot-up');
                    box.style.top = 'auto';
                    box.style.bottom = '40px';
                }

                // Smart Box Orientation: Avoid left/right screen edges
                if (yearIndex >= 7) {
                    box.style.left = 'auto';
                    box.style.right = '-20px';
                    box.style.transformOrigin = 'bottom right';
                    box.style.marginLeft = '0';
                    box.style.borderRadius = '8px 8px 0 8px';
                } else if (yearIndex === 6) {
                    box.style.left = 'auto';
                    box.style.right = '-20px';
                    box.style.transformOrigin = 'top right';
                    box.style.marginLeft = '0';
                    box.style.borderRadius = '8px 0 8px 8px';
                } else if (yearIndex <= 4) {
                    box.style.right = 'auto';
                    box.style.left = '-20px';
                    box.style.transformOrigin = 'bottom left';
                    box.style.marginLeft = '0';
                    box.style.borderRadius = '0 8px 8px 8px';
                } else {
                    box.style.right = 'auto';
                    box.style.left = '50%';
                    box.style.transformOrigin = 'top center';
                    box.style.marginLeft = '-210px'; // Half of 420px width
                    box.style.borderRadius = '8px';
                }

                anchor.style.left = point.x + 'px';
                anchor.style.top = point.y + 'px';
                anchor.style.display = 'block';
                
                anchor.classList.remove('animate');
                void anchor.offsetWidth; // Force Reflow
                anchor.classList.add('animate');
                anchor.style.opacity = '1';

                document.getElementById('concept-btn').onclick = () => {
                    anchor.style.opacity = '0';
                    setTimeout(() => {
                        anchor.style.display = 'none';
                        
                        // Smart-Chaining for Year 2: Move from Apex (0) to Forward (1) automatically
                        if (yearIndex === 2 && datasetIndex === 0 && !isRetrigger) {
                            showAcademicConcept(2, 1, false);
                        } else {
                            if (!isRetrigger) {
                                triggerSwoop(narratives[yearIndex], yearIndex);
                            } else {
                                isPaused = false;
                                updateButtons();
                            }
                        }
                    }, 500);
                };
            }
        }

        // --- Main Timeline Router ---
        function handleTimeChange(newVal) {
            if (isPaused) {
                slider.value = parseInt(yearLabel.innerText); 
                return;
            }

            let currentYearIndex = parseInt(newVal);
            let oldYearIndex = parseInt(yearLabel.innerText);

            // Reset flags if navigating backward
            if (currentYearIndex < oldYearIndex) {
                if (currentYearIndex < 2) { hasSeenBreach = false; seenConcepts[2] = false; }
                if (currentYearIndex < 3) seenConcepts[3] = false;
                if (currentYearIndex < 4) seenConcepts[4] = false;
                if (currentYearIndex < 5) seenConcepts[5] = false;
                if (currentYearIndex < 6) seenConcepts[6] = false;
                if (currentYearIndex < 7) hasSeenCrash = false;
                if (currentYearIndex < 8) seenConcepts[8] = false;
                if (currentYearIndex < 9) seenConcepts[9] = false;
                if (currentYearIndex < 12) hasSeenDeath = false;
            }

            // Year 2 cinematic
            if (currentYearIndex >= 2 && !hasSeenBreach) {
                hasSeenBreach = true;
                isPaused = true;
                slider.value = 2; 
                updateChartAndUI(2);

                const breachOverlay1 = document.getElementById('breach-overlay-1');
                breachOverlay1.style.display = 'flex';
                void breachOverlay1.offsetWidth; 
                breachOverlay1.style.opacity = '1';
                updateButtons();
                return;
            }
            
            // Year 7 cinematic
            if (currentYearIndex >= 7 && !hasSeenCrash) {
                hasSeenCrash = true;
                isPaused = true;
                slider.value = 7; 
                updateChartAndUI(7);

                const crashOverlay = document.getElementById('crash-overlay');
                crashOverlay.style.display = 'flex';
                setTimeout(() => { crashOverlay.style.opacity = '1'; }, 50);
                updateButtons();
                return;
            }
            
            // Year 12 cinematic
            if (currentYearIndex >= 12 && !hasSeenDeath) {
                hasSeenDeath = true;
                isPaused = true;
                slider.value = 12; 
                updateChartAndUI(12);

                const deathOverlay = document.getElementById('death-overlay');
                deathOverlay.style.display = 'flex';
                setTimeout(() => { 
                    deathOverlay.style.opacity = '1'; 
                    playOperatorMessage(); 
                }, 50);
                updateButtons();
                return;
            }

            // Dynamic Academic Concepts (Years 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 8, 9)
            // Notice Year 2 is NOT auto-triggered here, to protect the cinematic
            if (academicConcepts[currentYearIndex] && !seenConcepts[currentYearIndex] && currentYearIndex !== 2) {
                seenConcepts[currentYearIndex] = true;
                isPaused = true;
                slider.value = currentYearIndex;
                updateChartAndUI(currentYearIndex);
                
                // Determine which dataset to auto-show based on availability (defaults to Apex if both exist, otherwise Forward)
                let defaultDataset = academicConcepts[currentYearIndex][0] ? 0 : 1;
                setTimeout(() => { showAcademicConcept(currentYearIndex, defaultDataset, false); }, 450); 
                updateButtons();
                return;
            }

            // Standard Path
            slider.value = currentYearIndex;
            updateChartAndUI(currentYearIndex);
            triggerSwoop(narratives[currentYearIndex], currentYearIndex);
        }

        // --- Event Listeners ---
        slider.addEventListener('input', (e) => handleTimeChange(e.target.value));

        prevBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
            if (!isPaused && parseInt(slider.value) > 0) {
                handleTimeChange(parseInt(slider.value) - 1);
            }
        });

        nextBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
            if (!isPaused && parseInt(slider.value) < 13) {
                handleTimeChange(parseInt(slider.value) + 1);
            }
        });

        // --- Global Keyboard Navigation ---
        document.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
            if (e.key === 'ArrowRight') {
                const intro = document.getElementById('intro-overlay');
                const b1 = document.getElementById('breach-overlay-1');
                const b2 = document.getElementById('breach-overlay-2');
                const b3 = document.getElementById('breach-overlay-3');
                const crash = document.getElementById('crash-overlay');
                const death = document.getElementById('death-overlay');
                const concept = document.getElementById('concept-anchor');
                const float = document.getElementById('floating-narrative');

                if (intro.style.display !== 'none' && intro.style.opacity !== '0') { dismissIntro(); }
                else if (b1.style.display === 'flex' && b1.style.opacity !== '0') { nextBreachOverlay(1); }
                else if (b2.style.display === 'flex' && b2.style.opacity !== '0') { nextBreachOverlay(2); }
                else if (b3.style.display === 'flex' && b3.style.opacity !== '0') { finishBreachOverlay(); }
                else if (crash.style.display === 'flex' && crash.style.opacity !== '0') { dismissCrash(); }
                else if (death.style.display === 'flex' && death.style.opacity !== '0') { dismissDeath(); }
                else if (concept.style.display === 'block' && concept.style.opacity !== '0') { document.getElementById('concept-btn').click(); }
                else if (float.style.display === 'block' && float.style.opacity !== '0') { document.getElementById('fn-btn').click(); }
                else if (!isPaused && parseInt(slider.value) < 13) { document.getElementById('nextBtn').click(); }
                
            } else if (e.key === 'ArrowLeft') {
                const intro = document.getElementById('intro-overlay');
                const b1 = document.getElementById('breach-overlay-1');
                const b2 = document.getElementById('breach-overlay-2');
                const b3 = document.getElementById('breach-overlay-3');
                const crash = document.getElementById('crash-overlay');
                const death = document.getElementById('death-overlay');
                const concept = document.getElementById('concept-anchor');
                const float = document.getElementById('floating-narrative');

                if (intro.style.display !== 'none' && intro.style.opacity !== '0') { 
                    // Do nothing
                }
                else if (b3.style.display === 'flex' && b3.style.opacity !== '0') { 
                    b3.style.display = 'none';
                    b2.style.display = 'flex';
                }
                else if (b2.style.display === 'flex' && b2.style.opacity !== '0') { 
                    b2.style.display = 'none';
                    b1.style.display = 'flex';
                    b1.style.opacity = '1';
                }
                else if (b1.style.display === 'flex' && b1.style.opacity !== '0') { 
                    b1.style.opacity = '0';
                    setTimeout(() => { b1.style.display = 'none'; isPaused = false; handleTimeChange(1); }, 300);
                }
                else if (crash.style.display === 'flex' && crash.style.opacity !== '0') { 
                    crash.style.opacity = '0';
                    setTimeout(() => { crash.style.display = 'none'; isPaused = false; handleTimeChange(6); }, 300);
                }
                else if (death.style.display === 'flex' && death.style.opacity !== '0') { 
                    death.style.opacity = '0';
                    window.speechSynthesis.cancel();
                    setTimeout(() => { death.style.display = 'none'; isPaused = false; handleTimeChange(11); }, 300);
                }
                else if (concept.style.display === 'block' && concept.style.opacity !== '0') { 
                    concept.style.opacity = '0';
                    setTimeout(() => { 
                        concept.style.display = 'none'; 
                        isPaused = false; 
                        handleTimeChange(parseInt(slider.value) - 1); 
                    }, 300);
                }
                else if (float.style.display === 'block' && float.style.opacity !== '0') { 
                    float.style.opacity = '0';
                    setTimeout(() => {
                        float.style.display = 'none';
                        document.getElementById('narrative').style.opacity = '1';
                        isPaused = false;
                        let curr = parseInt(slider.value);
                        handleTimeChange(curr > 0 ? curr - 1 : 0);
                    }, 300);
                }
                else if (!isPaused && parseInt(slider.value) > 0) { 
                    document.getElementById('prevBtn').click(); 
                }
            }
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
